name: Login
auth_description: This service does not require authentication.

headers.name: EVA-User-Agent
headers.description: The user agent that is making these calls. Don't make this specific per device/browser but per application. This should be of the form: `MyFirstUserAgent/1.0.0`

headers.name: EVA-Requested-OrganizationUnitID
headers.description: The ID of the organization unit to run this request in.

headers.name: EVA-Requested-OrganizationUnit-Query
headers.description: The query that selects the organization unit to run this request in.

headers.name: EVA-IDs-Mode
headers.description: The IDs mode to run this request in. Currently only `ExternalIDs` is supported.

request_samples.name: CURL
request_samples.sample:
curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "EVA-User-Agent: MyFirstUserAgent/1.0.0" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
  --data '{
  "AsEmployee": true,
  "AuthenticationToken": "string",
  "CustomAuthenticateData": {
    "Challenge": "string",
    "Signature": "string",
    "UserID": 123
  },
  "CustomAuthenticatorType": "Passkey",
  "IdentificationCode": "string",
  "LanguageID": "string",
  "OrganizationUnitID": 123,
  "Password": "string",
  "SelectFirstOrganizationUnit": true,
  "TwoFactorAuthenticationToken": "string",
  "TwoFactorAuthenticator": "string",
  "TwoFactorRememberMe": true,
  "UseJwtTokens": true,
  "UserType": 4,
  "Username": "string",
  "VisibilityGroupID": 123
}' \
  https://euw.acme.test.eva-online.cloud/message/Login

E.name: provider
E.description: This is the ID of a `Provider`

B.name: AsEmployee
B.description: When set, the non-employees will be explicity filtered - used primarily when Customers and Employees are split, but can also be used to make sure no Customers can login

B.name: AuthenticationToken
CustomAuthenticateData
B.description: Data for the custom authenticator, if used

B.name: CustomAuthenticatorType
B.description:
Type of the custom authenticator, if used

Possible values:

* `Passkey`
* `IdentificationCode`
* `LIVEGUARD`
* `OpenID`

B.name: IdentificationCode
B.description: The employee code - used to login by QR or PIN

B.name: LanguageID
B.description:
The preferred Language for the session

This is the ID of a `Language`

B.name: OrganizationUnitID
B.description:
Used to login to a specific organization unit

This is the ID of a `OrganizationUnit`

B.name: SelectFirstOrganizationUnit
B.description: Login on the first OrganizationUnit in the tree where the user has the Login functionality

B.name: TwoFactorAuthenticator
B.description: The two-factor authenticator code that granted the confirmation token

B.name: TwoFactorRememberMe
B.description: If a successful two-factor authentication should be remembered on this IP address

B.name: UseJwtTokens
B.description: When enabled this service will return a JWT token and refresh token.

B.name: UserType
B.description:
Filters the available roles/functionalities when those are explicitly attached to a user type (only single flag values are allowed)
Flags enum, combine any of the below values:

* `0` - None
* `1` - Employee
* `2` - Customer
* `4` - Anonymous
* `8` - Business
* `17` - System
* `64` - Debtor
* `512` - Tester
* `1024` - RemovedByRequest
* `2048` - Api
* `4096` - Impersonated

B.name: Username
B.description: Primary identifier of the user, can be an `EmailAddress` or `Nickname`

B.name: VisibilityGroupID
B.description:
Used to login to a specific visibility group

This is the ID of a `VisibilityGroup`

G.description: A unique ID identifying this error.

G.name: Message
G.description: A human-readable message describing the error.

G.description: A unique ID identifying the request. Please provide this ID when contacting support.

G.description: A short description of the error type.

H.name: ExternalIDs
H.description: When using the `ExternalIDs` mode, this will hold the resolved external IDs.

H.name: IsAsyncResultAvailable
H.description: This is a flag indicating whether the async request is done. If it is `null`, it is not an async service. If it is `false`, the response is not yet available. Do not process the properties in that case. It is is `true` the properties are filled with the result of the call.

H.name: UnresolvedExternalIDs
H.description: When using the `ExternalIDs` mode, this will hold the external IDs we couldn't resolve.
